---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QRCodeGenerator from '../../components/tools/QRCodeGenerator';

const title = "Free QR Code Generator - Create QR Codes Online | Utility Hub";
const description = "Generate QR codes for any text or URL with our free online QR code generator. Download as PNG. No signup required.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical="/tools/qr-code-generator">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">QR Code Generator</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Generate QR codes for any text or URL instantly. Download your QR code as a PNG image. Free online QR code generator.</p>
      <QRCodeGenerator client:load />
      <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none mt-12">
        <h2>What is a QR Code Generator?</h2>
        <p>A QR code generator is a free online tool that creates QR (Quick Response) codes from text or URLs. QR codes are two-dimensional barcodes that can be scanned by smartphone cameras to access encoded information.</p>
        <h2>How to Use</h2>
        <p>Enter any text or URL, click "Generate QR Code," and download the QR code as a PNG image. The code can be scanned by any QR reader app.</p>
        <h2>Use Cases</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> Link to websites, promotions, and landing pages</li>
          <li><strong>Business cards:</strong> Share contact information digitally</li>
          <li><strong>Restaurants:</strong> Create digital menus accessible via QR codes</li>
          <li><strong>Events:</strong> Quick access to tickets and event information</li>
          <li><strong>WiFi sharing:</strong> Generate QR codes for WiFi network access</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Internal Links</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/tools/image-compressor">Image Compressor</a> - Compress images</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/image-resizer">Image Resizer</a> - Resize images</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/webp-converter">WebP Converter</a> - Convert to WebP</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/color-picker">Color Picker</a> - Pick and convert colors</li>
          <li><a href="/tools/base64-encoder-decoder">Base64 Encoder/Decoder</a> - Encode/decode</li>
        </ul>
        <h4>Frequently Asked Questions</h4>
        <p>Question: Can I use these QR codes commercially? Answer: Yes, generated QR codes are free for both personal and commercial use.</p>
        <p>Question: Do QR codes expire? Answer: No, QR codes are static images and never expire. The code contains your data directly.</p>
        <p>Question: What size are the generated QR codes? Answer: The generated QR codes are 250x250 pixels PNG images.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
</write_to_file>